                     <locus>ff.1b-125r</locus>
                     <title>Menahem Notebook</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">מחברת מנחם</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Meḥaberet Menaḥem</title>
                     <author key="person_97166551">
                        <persName>Mĕnaḥem ben Saruq, approximately 910-approximately 970</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">אבן סרוק, מנחם בן יעקב</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2">
                     <locus>ff.126r-126v</locus>
                     <title/>
                     <title xml:lang="he">הלכות כתיבת ספר תורה</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Halakhot ketivat Sefer Torah</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3">
                     <locus>ff.127r-164r</locus>
                     <title>Answers on the Menahem Notebook</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">תשובות על מחברת מנחם</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Teshovot 'al Meḥaberet Menaḥem</title>
                     <author key="person_71437573">
                        <persName>Dunash ben Labrat, active 10th century</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">דונש בן לברט</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                     <note>At the end (<locus>fol. 164</locus>) is a poem beginning with <lang xml:lang="he">נדר לאמר</lang>, with the acrostic of <persName key="person_7043">Natronai bar Sh'neor</persName> (the copyist?).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4">
                     <locus>ff.165r-208v</locus>
                     <title>The Book of Decisions by Rabbeinu Tam</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">הכרעות רבנו תם</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ha-kara'ot Rabenu Tam</title>
                     <author key="person_95487669">
                        <persName>Tam, Jacob ben Meir, approximately 1100-1171</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">יעקב בן מאיר (ר"ת)</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                     <note>Preceded by a poem beginning <lang xml:lang="he">ימין יי ערי</lang>, with the author's acrostic (half of the leaf is wanting), followed by a small introduction (injured).</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>                  
