                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Ashkenazic square scripts</summary>
                     <handNote>Written by different, contemporary, hands. 
                               <locus>Fols. 1v-81v</locus> by one hand, <locus>fols. 82-97</locus> by several different hands, <locus>fols.98r-125r</locus> by another hand. 
                        No. 3 (<locus>fols. 127r-164r</locus>)was copied in separate quires by one hand (apart from the beginning, <locus>fols. 127r-128r</locus>), which might very well be that of <persName key="person_7043"><lang xml:lang="he">נטרונאי בר שניאור</lang> (Natronai bar Sh'neor)</persName> - the poem on <locus>fol. 164r</locus> was written with a different quill but in the same style.
                               No. 4 (<locus>fols. 165-200</locus>) was written by the same hand as that which copied the end of no. 1 (<locus>fols. 98r-125r</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
